{
  "texts": [
    "The difference between similarity and relevance is one of the biggest challenges faced by retrieval systems, especially when working with large language models.",
    "While similarity measures help in identifying content that closely matches the query in terms of wording or context, it does not always guarantee that the retrieved information is truly relevant to the user's intent.",
    "This challenge often requires additional filtering or refinement techniques to ensure that retrieved results are not just similar but also meaningful and aligned with the specific needs of the query.",
    "Text-to-SQL is a powerful technique that bridges the gap between natural language queries and relational database systems by converting user inputs in plain text into executable SQL commands.",
    "This allows users to retrieve precise, structured information from databases without needing to understand SQL syntax [Liu et al., 2023]."
  ]
}